Concern:

The customer reported a bearing-type noise occurring when the vehicle is engaged in 4x4 mode.

 

Findings:

Our technician confirmed during a test drive that the noise is present in 4x4 mode and isolated it to the rear of the transfer case, near the connection with the rear driveshaft. Inspection ruled out other potential sources, confirming the transfer case as the issue.

 

Recommendation:

The technician recommends replacing the transfer case. The internal bearing causing the noise is not serviceable, and continued use could result in further damage. Replacing the transfer case will restore proper 4x4 operation and eliminate the noise.

notes.note: Customer called to say she is hearing a suspension noise from the front end. Said she has been hearing the noise since her vehicle purchase, and that she took it back to have them find the source of the noise, but they test drove the vehicle and only found something under the seat that they lubricated to stop the issue. Customer said she didn't hear any more for a short period following, but then noise started again. Took the vehicle to Nissan yesterday to have a full inspection done. Front lower control arm boots torn and no lubricant present, one front end link worn, both front shocks worn out, along with 17 other recommended services (injector service, brake fluid etc.). Explained there is no suspension coverage on the contract, she will need to speak to selling dealer to see if they will assist but we cannot put a claim through for this vehicle for these concerns. M.P.

notes.note:
Good afternoon, once again, thanks for the prior estimate for the replacement of the thermostat and water pump on Nas Anis' 2019 Benz. As mentioned before, the customer does not have any coverage for the thermostat, but does have coverage for the water pump. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for diagnostic fees, fluids, and all items listed besides the items required during the water pump replacement. The customer also has a $100 deductible.

Parts-$684.82
Labour-$494.00
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$140.25
Authorization-ALV13CJNWZ

Once the repair is complete, please send a copy of the final invoice for payment. 

Best regards, 

Matthew Puls

notes.note:
Good morning Lisa, thank you for your previous email with the estimate for the replacement of the stabilizer links on Gregory's Edge. Fortunately the stabilizer links are covered components under the customer's contract, although please note, we can only authorize for the replacement of the one that is actually broken, which you have indicated is the right front side. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees and shop supplies, as well as a $100 deductible + tax. Additionally, the labour for one side is 0.5, so this is the labour we used in the following payout:

Parts-$142.36
Labour-$49.50 (0.5 x $99/h)
Deductible-$100.00 + tax
Tax-$11.94
Authorization-FHRU7DJQ35

Total = $103.80

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards, 

Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster
